<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Cloud to Ground AI — v0.2 entitlements.

  App Sandbox is OFF for this dev build. Rationale:

    - The app must run `pgrep -f start_local_ai.sh` to detect the watcher,
      `which ollama` to detect the CLI binary, and `ollama list` to enumerate
      installed models. App Sandbox blocks all three.

    - The app calls http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags to probe Ollama liveness.
      The sandbox can allow this with com.apple.security.network.client,
      but the Process restrictions above already require sandbox off.

    - Distribution path is not yet decided (ACT-007). Until then, a
      notarized DMG with sandbox off is the cleanest dev workflow.

  When ACT-007 closes:
    - If "notarized DMG" wins: leave sandbox off, keep this file as-is.
    - If "Mac App Store" wins: turn sandbox on, add a privileged helper
      tool via SMJobBless or NSXPCService for the shell-outs, and add
      com.apple.security.network.client for the URLSession.

  See Cloud to Ground AI / Architecture Sketch §11 for the distribution
  trade study (when written).
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <false/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
